on the victim's neck.

564
00:41:31,269 --> 00:41:32,390
He bled out.

565
00:41:32,749 --> 00:41:35,189
Given the bloodstains
and blood volume at the scene,

566
00:41:35,350 --> 00:41:37,070
the carotid artery was likely lacerated.

567
00:41:37,550 --> 00:41:39,109
Rigor mortis is complete.

568
00:41:39,109 --> 00:41:40,870
The time of death was over 12 hours ago.

569
00:42:25,609 --> 00:42:29,102
♪Replacing the weight of tears
with that of sweat♪

570
00:42:32,896 --> 00:42:38,217
♪Covering the gunshot's sound
with wounds♪

571
00:42:40,290 --> 00:42:45,144
♪No one is born unyielding and strong♪

572
00:42:45,950 --> 00:42:49,097
♪But because someone
always rushes ahead♪

573
00:42:49,097 --> 00:42:52,201
♪To shield us from the storm♪

574
00:42:54,857 --> 00:42:59,991
♪When every extraordinary act
becomes routine♪

575
00:43:01,961 --> 00:43:07,593
♪Just to polish the badge
upon their shoulder♪

576
00:43:09,353 --> 00:43:12,937
♪Like light surging unseen
through the night♪

577
00:43:14,089 --> 00:43:21,529
♪Converging into your form♪

578
00:43:21,961 --> 00:43:24,639
♪Looking up♪

579
00:43:24,639 --> 00:43:28,178
♪Such dazzling glory♪

580
00:43:29,161 --> 00:43:31,721
♪Like hope♪

581
00:43:31,721 --> 00:43:35,654
♪Reaching out its arms♪

582
00:43:36,521 --> 00:43:39,173
♪Cloaked in light♪

583
00:43:39,173 --> 00:43:43,657
♪Alone, they charge ahead♪

584
00:43:43,657 --> 00:43:46,473
♪Traversing♪

585
00:43:46,473 --> 00:43:52,984
♪The battlefield of fate♪
